At the time of appointment by the department or the secretary, officers shall meet the minimum requirements established by this subsection:
Commercial vehicle enforcement officers shall:
Meet at least one (1) of the following education or experience requirements:
Have completed at least fifty-four (54) semester hours with a college or university;
Possess at least two (2) years experience as a commercial vehicle inspector under the North American Standard Requirements;
Possess at least two (2) years experience as a full-time sworn law enforcement officer; or
Possess at least two (2) years experience in military duty;
Be of good moral character and capable of successfully meeting the physical fitness standards established by the commissioner; and
Meet the minimum qualifications for becoming a certified peace officer as provided by KRS 15.382;
Arson investigator officers shall:
Possess at least one (1) year of law enforcement, police, criminal, fire, or arson investigation experience; and
Meet the minimum qualifications for becoming a certified peace officer as provided by KRS 15.382;
Hazardous devices investigator officers shall:
Possess at least five (5) years of experience involving explosives or hazardous devices used in the areas of law enforcement, the military, or firefighting; and
Meet the minimum qualifications for becoming a certified peace officer as provided by KRS 15.382; and
Facilities security officers shall be commissioned as special law enforcement officers under KRS 61.900 to 61.930.
